# Ops Gateway

## Identity

The operational layer that manages the "hands" of the system — container orchestration, data backups, vector reindexing, cache management, and production verification.

## Docker Compose Topology

| File | Purpose | Services |
|------|---------|----------|
| `docker-compose.dev.yml` | Local development | mongodb, backend, redis, frontend, payload_cms, admin_frontend |
| `docker-compose.prod.yml` | Production deployment | Full stack with production configs |
| `docker-compose.prod-local.yml` | Local production testing | Production-like on localhost |
| `docker-compose.override.yml` | Dev overrides | Volume mounts, hot reload |
| `payload_cms/docker-compose.yml` | CMS standalone | Payload CMS + MongoDB |
| `monitoring/docker-compose.monitoring.yml` | Observability | Prometheus, Grafana |

### Service Ports (dev)

| Service | Host Port | Container Port |
|---------|-----------|----------------|
| MongoDB | 27017 | 27017 |
| Backend (FastAPI) | 8000 | 8000 |
| Redis | 6379 | 6379 |
| Frontend | 3000 | 3000 |
| Payload CMS | 3001 | 3000 |
| Admin Frontend | 3002 | 3000 |

## Scripts by Category

### Lifecycle

- `run-dev.sh` / `run-prod.sh` / `run-prod-local.sh` — start stacks
- `down-prod.sh` / `shutdown-prod.sh` — stop stacks
- `rebuild-backend.sh` / `rebuild-frontend.sh` / `rebuild-admin-frontend.sh` — targeted rebuilds

### Data & Backup

- `backup-mongodb.sh` — MongoDB dump
- `archive-encrypt-mongodb-backup.sh` — encrypted archive
- `backup-and-stage-for-github.sh` — prepare backup for version control

### Reindex

- `reindex_vectors.py` — full vector store rebuild
- `reindex_with_faq.py` — rebuild with FAQ parent documents

Run these after CMS schema changes, embedding model changes, or chunking strategy updates.

### Cache Management

- `clear-semantic-cache.py` / `semantic-cache-stats.py` — semantic cache ops
- `clear-redis-settings.sh` — reset Redis admin settings
- `refresh-suggested-cache.sh` — refresh suggested questions cache
- `clear-prometheus-data.sh` / `reset-all-metrics.sh` — monitoring reset

### Verification

- `verify-production-builds.sh` — validate all containers built correctly
- `verify-https-enforcement.sh` — check TLS config
- `verify-mongo-auth.sh` — validate MongoDB authentication

### Monitoring

- `check-prometheus-metrics.sh` — query Prometheus
- `test-monitoring-ports.sh` — verify monitoring stack connectivity
- `backend-uptime-check.sh` / `install-backend-uptime-check.sh` — uptime monitoring

## Environment Files

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `.env.docker.dev` | Docker dev environment variables |
| `.env.docker.prod` | Docker production environment variables |
| `backend/.env` | Backend secrets (API keys) |
| `payload_cms/.env` | CMS secrets (PAYLOAD_SECRET) |

**Never commit these files.** They are in `.gitignore`.

## Key Rules

- Always specify which services a script change affects
- Reindex scripts must be run after any change to CMS collections or embedding models
- Test scripts against dev stack before running on production
- When modifying Docker Compose files, validate with `docker compose config` before committing
- Backup scripts should be tested with restore verification
